WHAT I WAS THINKING.

27:11.163 --> 27:16.769
I'M NOT GOING TO TELL YOU
THAT JEREMY JONES IS AN ANGEL,

27:16.803 --> 27:20.072
BUT HE IS NOT GUILTY OF
THE CRIMES HE IS CHARGED WITH.

27:20.106 --> 27:23.209
NEITHER THOSE
AGAINST INDIVIDUALS,

27:23.242 --> 27:25.144
NOR THE SUPPOSEDLY
WORSE CRIME

27:25.177 --> 27:28.247
OF THINKING BAD THOUGHTS.

27:32.985 --> 27:36.889
- MR. MURPHY, WHERE
DID YOU MEET THE DEFENDANT?

27:36.923 --> 27:41.393
- AT A BAR
CALLED NEW YORK JUNK.

27:41.427 --> 27:44.864
- WHAT KIND OF BAR
IS THAT?

27:44.897 --> 27:47.066
- IT'S A GAY BAR.

27:47.099 --> 27:49.435
- WHAT WERE YOU DOING THERE?

27:49.468 --> 27:53.439
- I WAS LOOKING
FOR COMPANIONSHIP

27:53.472 --> 27:55.241
FOR THE EVENING.

27:55.274 --> 27:57.810
- WHAT KIND
OF COMPANIONSHIP?

27:57.844 --> 28:00.246
- SEXUAL COMPANIONSHIP.

28:00.279 --> 28:03.783
- DID THE DEFENDANT
APPROACH YOU, MR. ARMSTRONG,

28:03.816 --> 28:06.218
OR DID YOU APPROACH HIM?

28:06.252 --> 28:07.954
- HE APPROACHED ME.

28:07.987 --> 28:10.056
- AND WHAT HAPPENED THEN?

28:10.089 --> 28:13.425
- WE TALKED FOR A WHILE,
THEN DECIDED TO GO TO A HOTEL.

28:13.459 --> 28:15.762
- AND WHAT HAPPENED THERE?

28:15.795 --> 28:20.066
- WE BEGAN TO HAVE RELATIONS.

28:20.099 --> 28:22.034
- AND WERE YOU WILLING,
MR. JACKSON?

28:22.068 --> 28:23.302
- AT FIRST.

28:23.335 --> 28:25.104
- BUT ONLY AT FIRST?
- YES.

28:25.137 --> 28:27.106
HE WANTED ME TO DO THINGS
I WASN'T COMFORTABLE WITH.

28:27.139 --> 28:31.477
- DID YOU OBJECT?
- YES. VERY MUCH.

28:31.510 --> 28:33.846
I TRIED TO LEAVE.
- AND WHY DIDN'T YOU?

28:33.880 --> 28:37.016
- HE HAD TIED ME DOWN.
I COULDN'T EVEN MOVE.

28:37.049 --> 28:38.818
- HE TIED ME TO THE BED.

28:38.851 --> 28:41.453
FORCED HIMSELF INTO ME.

28:41.487 --> 28:43.389
HE WAS CALLING ME NAMES,
BEATING ME.

28:43.422 --> 28:45.825
- HE WAS VICIOUS.
OUT OF CONTROL.

28:45.858 --> 28:47.994
- THE MORE IT HURT ME,
THE HAPPIER HE WAS.

28:48.027 --> 28:50.362
- HE LEFT ME TIED UP.
HE TOOK MY WALLET.

28:50.396 --> 28:52.899
- AND HE KEPT SAYING,
"HOW DOES IT FEEL TO...

28:52.932 --> 28:54.767
BE THE FAG?"

29:02.909 --> 29:05.377
- THAT WAS BRAVE.
- YEAH. REALLY.

29:05.411 --> 29:06.445
NOW THE WHOLE WORLD KNOWS.

29:06.478 --> 29:07.980
- MELISSA.
- DON'T.

29:08.014 --> 29:09.381
DO YOU KNOW WHAT
IT WAS LIKE FOR ME

29:09.415 --> 29:11.217
SITTING IN THERE
LISTENING TO THAT?

29:11.250 --> 29:13.219
- MAYBE YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE COME.
- OH, THAT WOULD BE PERFECT.

29:13.252 --> 29:15.354
SO THE WHOLE WORLD KNOWS,
BUT I DON'T.

29:15.387 --> 29:17.824
JUST LIKE BEFORE, RIGHT?

29:17.857 --> 29:20.492
- 16 YEARS.
- MR. MURPHY--

29:20.526 --> 29:23.896
- DON'T EVEN TRY.

29:27.867 --> 29:29.335
- I'M A GAY MAN.

29:29.368 --> 29:31.170
I LIKE TO GO OUT
AND I LIKE TO MEET PEOPLE.

29:31.203 --> 29:34.240
- YOU LIKE TO MEET
PEOPLE FOR SEX.

29:34.273 --> 29:36.843
- I ENJOY SEX.
IT MAKES ME FEEL ALIVE.

29:36.876 --> 29:38.410
I NEVER DO IT
TO HURT ANYONE.

29:38.444 --> 29:39.912
- JEREMY, THAT'S NOT
WHAT WE'RE HEARING

29:39.946 --> 29:42.048
FROM THE WITNESSES
AGAINST YOU.

29:42.081 --> 29:44.450
- I KNOW. BUT CHARLES
AND CURTIS AND ETHAN--

29:44.483 --> 29:47.286
WHEN THEY MET ME, THEY WANTED
TO SPEND TIME WITH ME.

29:47.319 --> 29:48.587
- THEY TRIED
TO PICK YOU UP?

29:48.620 --> 29:50.289
- YES.

29:50.322 --> 29:52.324
AND THEY'RE ALL
IN THE CLOSET, I GUESS,

29:52.358 --> 29:53.893
AND NOW THEY'RE EMBARRASSED,

29:53.926 --> 29:55.027
AND I THINK
THAT'S WHY THEY'RE LYING.

29:55.061 --> 29:56.462
- MOVE TO STRIKE.

29:56.495 --> 29:58.130
WE'RE NOT HERE TO LISTEN
TO THE DEFENDANT'S

29:58.164 --> 29:59.398
PSYCHOLOGICAL THEORIES.

29:59.431 --> 30:01.567
- SUSTAINED.
THE JURY WILL DISREGARD.

30:01.600 --> 30:04.503
- JEREMY, DID YOU FORCE
ANY OF THOSE MEN

30:04.536 --> 30:07.139
TO DO ANYTHING
THEY DIDN'T WANT TO DO?

30:07.173 --> 30:09.308
- NO. THEY CAME ON TO ME.

30:09.341 --> 30:11.543
THEY SUGGESTED
GOING TO HOTELS.

30:11.577 --> 30:13.145
CHARLES STARTED
BUYING ME DRINKS.

30:13.179 --> 30:15.581
HE TOLD ME
I HAD BEAUTIFUL EYES.

30:15.614 --> 30:17.483
HE WAS REALLY NICE.

30:17.516 --> 30:20.519
- WELL, SOME
OF YOUR ACTIVITIES--

30:20.552 --> 30:22.889
[sighs]
THE SEXUAL ONES,

30:22.922 --> 30:25.491
ARE A LITTLE UNCONVENTIONAL.

30:25.524 --> 30:27.226
- SEX GAMES.

30:27.259 --> 30:29.595
MEN LIKE THAT--
WHEN THEY LET LOOSE,

30:29.628 --> 30:31.597
THEY CAN GET
A LITTLE KINKY.

30:31.630 --> 30:34.233
THEY'VE VERY BOTTLED UP.

30:34.266 --> 30:35.434
I WAS EVEN SURPRISED
BY SOME OF THE THINGS

30:35.467 --> 30:36.502
THAT THEY WANTED.

30:36.535 --> 30:38.204
- THE THINGS
THEY SAY YOU TOOK?

30:38.237 --> 30:39.505
- GIFTS.

30:39.538 --> 30:41.874
I'M UNEMPLOYED
AND THEY'RE ALL RICH.

30:41.908 --> 30:43.242
I WAS EMBARRASSED
TO TAKE ANYTHING,

30:43.275 --> 30:45.144
BUT I COULDN'T
AFFORD TO SAY NO.

30:45.177 --> 30:47.546
I ONLY WISH THAT I HAD.

30:47.579 --> 30:51.951
- THANK YOU.

30:51.984 --> 30:53.552
OH, ONE MORE THING.

30:53.585 --> 30:56.622
JEREMY, DO YOU HATE GAYS?

30:56.655 --> 30:58.958
- [chuckles]
OF COURSE NOT.

30:58.991 --> 31:01.427
THAT'S WHO I AM.

31:01.460 --> 31:04.596
- RIGHT.

31:07.599 --> 31:12.071
- SO, MR. JONES,
YOU DON'T HATE GAYS?

31:12.104 --> 31:13.072
- OF COURSE NOT.

31:13.105 --> 31:14.306
- BUT YOUR GAY SEX PARTNERS

31:14.340 --> 31:16.575
