A VERDICT AS A MATTER OF LAW.

35:09.475 --> 35:13.445
AND THAT NEVER LOOKS GOOD
FOR A PROSECUTOR, DOES IT?

35:18.517 --> 35:20.386
- JUDGE GAVE ME A CHOICE.

35:20.419 --> 35:22.188
DROP THE HATE CRIME CHARGES
OR SHE'D DO IT FOR ME.

35:22.221 --> 35:23.489
- WE ALWAYS KNEW
THAT WAS A STRETCH.

35:23.522 --> 35:24.823
- BUT THE RAPES,
THE ROBBERIES.

35:24.856 --> 35:26.558
I MEAN, THOSE LOOK
PRETTY DAMN CLEAR.

35:26.592 --> 35:28.260
- MAYBE TO YOU.

35:28.294 --> 35:30.362
THE JURY'S BEEN
DELIBERATING FOR THREE DAYS.

35:30.396 --> 35:32.398
AND THEY KEEP POPPING OUT
TO SAY THAT THEY'RE DEADLOCKED.

35:32.431 --> 35:36.368
[cell phone buzzes]
AH. HERE THEY COME AGAIN.

35:42.774 --> 35:44.910
- STILL NO PROGRESS,
YOUR HONOR,

35:44.943 --> 35:47.446
AND THINGS ARE GETTING
A LITTLE ANTAGONISTIC

35:47.479 --> 35:48.880
IN THE JURY ROOM.

35:48.914 --> 35:51.517
NONE OF US FEEL THERE'S
ANY POINT IN CONTINUING.

35:51.550 --> 35:53.452
- ARE THERE ANY CHARGES
IN WHICH YOU HAVE BEEN ABLE

35:53.485 --> 35:54.820
TO AGREE?

35:54.853 --> 35:57.223
- YES. ON THE COUNTS
OF UNLAWFUL IMPRISONMENT,

35:57.256 --> 35:58.724
WE FIND THE DEFENDANT GUILTY.

35:58.757 --> 36:00.326
- VERY WELL.

36:00.359 --> 36:02.794
- ON THE OTHER CHARGES,
I DECLARE A MISTRIAL.

36:02.828 --> 36:05.331
A DATE FOR SENTENCING
WILL BE SET ON THE CONVICTIONS.

36:05.364 --> 36:08.334
- YOUR HONOR,
I REQUEST A HEARING ON BAIL,

36:08.367 --> 36:09.735
PENDING SENTENCING,
SINCE THE ONLY CONVICTIONS

36:09.768 --> 36:12.738
ARE RELATIVELY MINOR,
REMOVING ANY INCENTIVE TO FLEE.

36:12.771 --> 36:15.841
- SO ORDERED.

36:24.916 --> 36:27.619
- YOU WANT ME
TO TESTIFY AGAIN?

36:27.653 --> 36:31.623
- FOR UNLAWFUL IMPRISONMENT,
JONES WILL GET A YEAR AT MOST.

36:31.657 --> 36:33.425
I CAN RETRY HIM
ON THE ROBBERIES AND RAPES

36:33.459 --> 36:34.960
AND WE STAND
A PRETTY GOOD CHANCE IF YOU--

36:34.993 --> 36:36.628
- NO.

36:36.662 --> 36:38.264
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
THE OTHER GUYS ARE GONNA DO,

36:38.297 --> 36:39.331
BUT I'M NOT
TESTIFYING AGAIN.

36:39.365 --> 36:40.599
- I KNOW THIS
HAS BEEN DIFFICULT--

36:40.632 --> 36:42.434
- DIFFICULT?

36:42.468 --> 36:44.370
I'M LIVING IN A HOTEL.

36:44.403 --> 36:46.938
MY 12-YEAR-OLD SON
IS GETTING BULLIED IN SCHOOL.

36:46.972 --> 36:48.540
THE YOUNGER KIDS,
THEY DON'T KNOW WHAT'S GOING ON.

36:48.574 --> 36:52.244
THEY JUST--THEY JUST
SEE THEIR MOTHER CRYING.

36:52.278 --> 36:56.315
- MR. MURPHY,
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING.

36:56.348 --> 36:58.750
- FOR WHO?
FOR WHAT?

36:58.784 --> 37:00.419
- JEREMY JONES
IS A MURDERER.

37:00.452 --> 37:03.789
- WELL, THEN WHY DON'T YOU
GET HIM FOR MURDER?

37:07.859 --> 37:09.495
[door closes]

37:09.528 --> 37:11.297
- NOT AN ENTIRELY
UNREASONABLE QUESTION.

37:11.330 --> 37:12.898
- HE'S RIGHT.
LET'S GET HIM FOR MURDER.

37:12.931 --> 37:14.566
- THAT WOULD BE DELIGHTFUL.

37:14.600 --> 37:16.468
HAVE YOU CONJURED UP
SOME EVIDENCE?

37:16.502 --> 37:19.538
- WE KNOW THAT JONES
STOLE FROM HIS VICTIMS

37:19.571 --> 37:22.040
